com.versant.common.dataservice
Class VDSValue

java.lang.Object
  com.versant.common.dataservice.VDSValue
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
public class VDSValue
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

This class is a generic container to hold all types of data. It provides the interfaces to retrieve the data in the appropriate format. The VDSObject class uses this container to hold the data. The value of an object attribute is represented by this interface.

See Also:
, Serialized Form

VDSValue

public VDSValue(java.util.Vector vdsvalues)
Constructor. creates VDSValue object of type struct. the value is a vector of VDSValue or an array of VDSValue ( i.e. VDSValue[]). The values may be of different VDSJavaDataTypes. This contains a sequence of VDSValues. Because of this, it can represent almost any arbitrary data structure by using recursion.

Parameters:
vdsvalues - Vector of VDSValue ( for a row) or VDSValue[](to represent table)
